  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSE Mainstreaming Circular Economy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Municipal solid waste is a serious challenge for India due to poor management systems. India generates 62 milllion tonnes of solid waste annually and most of it reaches a land fill.  The Centre for Science and Environment (CSE), a leading environmental NGO in India, will demonstrate that municipal solid waste can be segregated and composted at source and that the plastic waste can be recycled. CSE will train 100 municipalities on circular economy and develop 2 municipalities in India on source segregation of waste. It would develop 30 model schools as model zero waste school campuses. The project would also include training on circular economy, recycling and research on quality of compost from municipal waste.</narrative>
  </description>
